        <item>
          <title>How to Install Latest Firefox 4 and Firefox 3 in Ubuntu ?</title>
          <link>https://www.shafiq.in/2011/02/07/how-to-install-latest-firefox-4-and-firefox-3-in-ubuntu/</link>
          <pubDate>Mon, 07 Feb 2011 12:14:17 UTC</pubDate>
          <author></author>
          <guid>https://www.shafiq.in/2011/02/07/how-to-install-latest-firefox-4-and-firefox-3-in-ubuntu/</guid>
          <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to Install Latest Firefox 4 and Firefox 3 in &lt;a class=&#34;zem_slink&#34; title=&#34;Ubuntu (operating system)&#34; rel=&#34;homepage&#34; href=&#34;http://www.ubuntu.com/&#34;&gt;Ubuntu&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do the following in Terminal to install latest &lt;a class=&#34;zem_slink&#34; title=&#34;Mozilla Firefox 4&#34; rel=&#34;homepage&#34; href=&#34;http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/firefox/beta/&#34;&gt;Firefox 4.0&lt;/a&gt; and Firefox 3 in Ubuntu.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;zem_slink&#34; title=&#34;Sudo&#34; rel=&#34;homepage&#34; href=&#34;http://www.sudo.ws/&#34;&gt;sudo&lt;/a&gt; add-apt-repository ppa:ubuntu-mozilla-daily/ppa &amp;amp;&amp;amp; sudo &lt;a class=&#34;zem_slink&#34; title=&#34;Advanced Packaging Tool&#34; rel=&#34;homepage&#34; href=&#34;http://wiki.debian.org/Apt&#34;&gt;apt-get&lt;/a&gt; update
sudo apt-get install firefox-4.0
sudo apt-get install firefox&lt;/pre&gt;
</description>
        </item>
      
    
      
        <item>
          <title>ERROR: `phpize&#39; failed [solved]</title>
          <link>https://www.shafiq.in/2011/01/17/error-phpize-failed-solved/</link>
          <pubDate>Mon, 17 Jan 2011 12:21:05 UTC</pubDate>
          <author></author>
          <guid>https://www.shafiq.in/2011/01/17/error-phpize-failed-solved/</guid>
          <description>&lt;p&gt;If you get the following error install the development files of &lt;a class=&#34;zem_slink&#34; title=&#34;PHP&#34; rel=&#34;homepage&#34; href=&#34;http://www.php.net/&#34;&gt;PHP&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;running: &lt;a class=&#34;zem_slink&#34; title=&#34;PHPize&#34; rel=&#34;homepage&#34; href=&#34;http://www.phpize.com&#34;&gt;phpize&lt;/a&gt;
sh: phpize: not found
ERROR: `phpize&#39; failed&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On Ubuntu/Debian you could run the following line in the terminal :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;zem_slink&#34; title=&#34;Advanced Packaging Tool&#34; rel=&#34;homepage&#34; href=&#34;http://wiki.debian.org/Apt&#34;&gt;apt-get&lt;/a&gt; install php5-dev&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;font-family:Georgia, &#39;Times New Roman&#39;, &#39;Bitstream Charter&#39;, Times, serif;line-height:19px;white-space:normal;font-size:13px;&#34;&gt;that&#39;s it :)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
      
    
      
